<FIRST>r i PM-Malaysia-Pirates     06-17 0208</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Malaysia-Pirates,0213</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report: Nine Killed When Pirates Attack Refugee Boat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nine refugees were killed when
modern-day pirates in a speedboat raided a boat full of Filipinos, a
newspaper reported today.
   The New Straits Times, quoting police sources in Sabah state,
said the attack took place Wednesday near Pulau Gaya island. It said
the boat was carrying 33 people, including 11 women and children.
   Such pirates have killed hundreds of refugees in Southeast Asian
waters this year. On April 16, pirates off Malaysia set fire to a
refugee boat and killed 130 Vietnamese in a rampage of rape,
shootings and clubbings, relief officials in Malaysia said.
   
   The survivors of the latest attack told police seven heavily
armed pirates in a speedboat approached their vessel and fired
several shots in the air, forcing the skipper to stop, the newspaper
said. The pirates came on board and cart away the refugee's cash and
valuables, it said.
   The pirates then forced nine males, including the skipper, to one
side of the boat and opened fire, killing them, the newspaper said.
The pirates escaped after breaking the boat's rudder, the report
said.
   Fishermen rescued the survivors Thursday when they heard cries
for help, the newspaper said.
</TEXT>
