<SECOND>PM-Kenya-Crash,0156</SECOND>
<HEAD>Four Americans, Kenyan Pilot Killed in Air Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four U.S. tourists and their Kenyan pilot
were killed when their airplane crashed in the forested Aberdares
mountains of central Kenya, authorities said today.
   A spokesman for the U.S. Embassy in Nairobi confirmed the Friday
morning crash of the Air Kenya craft but declined to identify the
victims until next of kin had been notified.
   John Buckley, managing director of Air Kenya, said the crash of
the twin-engine Italian-made Partenavia occurred while on a flight
from the capital to the provincial town of Nyeri, 92 miles north.
   The English-language Daily Nation newspaper quoted witnesses
today as saying the aircraft crashed in bad weather about 12 miles
from its destination. Police needed a tractor to recover the bodies,
according to the newspaper.
   Buckley said the cause of the accident was under investigation by
the Directorate of Civil Aviation.
