<FIRST>r i PM-Soviet-Quakes     06-17 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Soviet-Quakes,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Moderate Earthquakes Rock Armenia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Several moderate earthquakes struck an area of
Armenia that was devastated by an earthquake last year, but no new
casualties or damage were reported, the Tass news agency reported
today.
   Tremors measuring 3 to 5.5 on the 12-point Soviet earthquake
scale were recorded Friday in Kirovakan, Aparan, Razdan and
Leninakan, the region where nearly 25,000 people were killed in an
earthquake on Dec. 7, Tass said.
   An temblor of 5 points is capable of swaying buildings and
cracking walls but is not considered life-threatening, according to
Soviet seismic experts.
   Other tremors, registering up to 2.5 points, were recorded this
morning by the seismograph station in Kirovakan.
   ``These are secondary tremors in the given zone,'' Tass said.
</TEXT>
