<FIRST>r i AM-Portugal-Crash     06-17 0163</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Portugal-Crash,0168</SECOND>
<HEAD>Helicopter Crashes on Beach, Kills Five</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LISBON, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Portuguese air force helicopter crashed
and burned Saturday at the Atlantic beach resort of Figueira da Foz,
killing the craft's five occupants, an official said.
   The French-made Alouette III copter crashed while trying to land
on the beach in thick fog, an air force spokesman.
   The helicopter was carrying two air force officers and three
members of a television crew who were filming a documentary, an
official of the RTP state televison network said.
   All five were killed instantly, said Antonio Murta, fire chief of
Figueira da Foz, 120 miles north of Lisbon.
   The helicopter was about 50 yards above the sand when it suddenly
fell and burst into flames on impact, said Feliz Pinot, a witness.
   Another witness said people were on the sand when the copter
crashed. There were no reported injuries among those on the beach.
   The helicopter was from an air force base at Tancos.
</TEXT>
