<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Indonesia-Gas     06-17 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Indonesia-Gas,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fumes From Abandoned Gas Well Kill Two, Injure 35</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: One name cq for Kusyudono in 2nd graf.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Toxic fumes seeped from an abandoned
natural gas well on the island of Borneo, killing two people and
injuring 35, police said Saturday.
   The two men were found dead near the well on Friday, according to
local police spokesman Lt. Col. Kusyudono. Fumes from the well also
killed cows and buffaloes, and their carcasses were found in a
nearby forest, he said.
   The 1,500 residents near the well were evacuated while police and
employees of the state-owned oil corporation, Pertamina, stopped the
gas leakage.
   The well had been abandoned since 1976. It was not immediately
known what caused the leak.
</TEXT>
