<HEAD>Plane Plunges Into Lake Crowded With Windsurfers</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: IJzerman is CQ throughout</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOOFDDORP, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The pilot of a small plane died
Saturday when his craft plunged into a lake crowded with windsurfers
and swimmers, police said.
   A second occupant of the plane was hospitalized in serious
condition, according to police spokesman Dirk IJzerman. No further
injuries were reported, he said.
   The cause of the crash was not immediately known, IJzerman said.
   The accident occurred at a recreational area near Hoofddorp. The
accident might have been far worse if the aircraft had crashed on
the lake's shore, where 1,000 people were watching an equestrian
event, IJzerman said.
