<HEAD>Jurors in Swindall Perjury Trial Adjourn Until Monday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jurors in the federal perjury trial of former Rep.
Pat Swindall deliberated six hours Saturday before going home for
the weekend.
   The jury, which will return Monday morning, spent the day in the
Richard B. Russell Federal Building amid exhibits that included
thousands of pages of transcripts.
   Swindall faces nine counts of perjury. He's accused of lying on
Feb. 2, 1988, to a federal grand jury investigating his 1987
