launderer, and with an associate later convicted of money laundering.
   Swindall, 38, faces 10 months to five years in prison on each
count.
   The jury began its deliberations Friday afternoon, following
closing arguments and extensive instructions from U.S. District
Judge Richard C. Freeman on the laws involved in the case.
   Jurors worked for an hour Friday, and resumed their deliberations
Saturday morning.
