<FIRST>r i AM-BRF---Spain-Peseta     06-17 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF---Spain-Peseta,0144</SECOND>
<HEAD>Spain To Join European Monetary System</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government said Friday it will integrate
the peseta in the European Monetary System's exchange mechanism next
week.
   Economy Minister Carlos Solchaga said the action will make the
nation's currency more stable, help reduce Spain's balance of
payments deficit and increase the competitiveness of its exports.
   He called it ``the most transcendent decision'' for Spain since
it joined the European Economic Community in January 1986.
   Economy Ministry officials said the participation of the peseta
in the European Currency Unit's basket of currencies will be fixed
at a meeting of the EEC Council of Ministers in Luxembourg Monday.
   When Spain enters the European Monetary System it will be the
ninth member among the 12 EEC nations. Britain, Greece and Portugal
do not participate in the system.
</TEXT>
